{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/Portfolio/polkadot_dev_camp/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Yoon's Dev ","author":"[JeongSoYoun]","siteUrl":"https://jeongsoyoun.github.io","comment":{"utterances":"JeongSoYoun/JeongSoYoun.github.io"},"sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":"yoon"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"39b04b3b-04ee-5b0e-9af5-af5ed1cf764b","excerpt":"Polkadot Dev Camp Project Asset Tracking System based on Substrate Goal The aim of this project is to build a shipment tracking and verification using Substrate. The Minimum Viable Product (MVP) will have the functionality to create a shipment with a unique ID and a predefined…","html":"<p><br /><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 40%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"dev camp\" title=\"dev camp\" src=\"/static/d8098b1340468285b9ec2dd464035229/c1b63/dev_camp.png\" srcset=\"/static/d8098b1340468285b9ec2dd464035229/5a46d/dev_camp.png 300w,\n/static/d8098b1340468285b9ec2dd464035229/0a47e/dev_camp.png 600w,\n/static/d8098b1340468285b9ec2dd464035229/c1b63/dev_camp.png 1200w,\n/static/d8098b1340468285b9ec2dd464035229/2cefc/dev_camp.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span></p>\n<br />\n<blockquote>\n<p>Polkadot Dev Camp Project</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Asset Tracking System based on Substrate</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"goal\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#goal\" aria-label=\"goal permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Goal</h2>\n<p>The aim of this project is to build a shipment tracking and verification using <em>Substrate</em>. The Minimum Viable Product (MVP) will have the functionality to create a shipment with a unique ID and a predefined static route. The verification component will consist of generating a secret key for the next transit point of the shipment at every transit point. Since we’re using <em>blockchain</em>, it is fully end-to-end system and transparency.</p>\n<p>Only the owner node can accept the package and it then becomes fully responsible for delivering the package to the next temporary owner. More general purpose than most IOT based blockchains. It doesn’t require an IOT device. Blockchain is agnostic to the choice of generated physical tags - anything from Barcode or QR code to RFID works.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 53.666666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"dev camp design1\" title=\"dev camp design1\" src=\"/static/823200e6a3eac8eb89502f4574dd5310/c1b63/dev_camp_design1.png\" srcset=\"/static/823200e6a3eac8eb89502f4574dd5310/5a46d/dev_camp_design1.png 300w,\n/static/823200e6a3eac8eb89502f4574dd5310/0a47e/dev_camp_design1.png 600w,\n/static/823200e6a3eac8eb89502f4574dd5310/c1b63/dev_camp_design1.png 1200w,\n/static/823200e6a3eac8eb89502f4574dd5310/cd138/dev_camp_design1.png 1220w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<br>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 53.666666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"dev camp design2\" title=\"dev camp design2\" src=\"/static/e1942d01db05d2a1fb7d4c6268d6c87a/c1b63/dev_camp_design2.png\" srcset=\"/static/e1942d01db05d2a1fb7d4c6268d6c87a/5a46d/dev_camp_design2.png 300w,\n/static/e1942d01db05d2a1fb7d4c6268d6c87a/0a47e/dev_camp_design2.png 600w,\n/static/e1942d01db05d2a1fb7d4c6268d6c87a/c1b63/dev_camp_design2.png 1200w,\n/static/e1942d01db05d2a1fb7d4c6268d6c87a/5c744/dev_camp_design2.png 1206w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"design\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#design\" aria-label=\"design permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Design</h2>\n<br />\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Manager</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>One account that manages a number of <em>transit points</em> and has the power to <strong>add</strong> or <strong>remove</strong> transit points. In Substrate, this would be <strong><em>sudo</em></strong> account who is the god-like in Substrate-based blockchain. We check this sudo account using <em>ensure-root</em> macros.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Transit Nodes</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Each transit point has a unique id and serves as both a <strong>sender</strong> and <strong>receiver</strong> of packages. In the MVP, each originating transit point also sets the route and calls a blockchain function that <strong>creates a key</strong> and <em>sets the next transit point as the next owner</em> of the package.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Customers</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In this implementation customers can only access the state of the chain for the current location and status of the package. State will be stored in <strong>storage</strong> in Substrate.</p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"implementation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#implementation\" aria-label=\"implementation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Implementation</h2>\n<p>Let there be:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>N transit points { TP1, TP2, …, TPN}</li>\n<li>\n<p>A shipment with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>route = { TP4, TP8, TP11 }</li>\n<li>uid = 112</li>\n<li>key = X</li>\n<li>owner = TP8</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Package with a physical tag and seal that can be scanned to get the key</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When TP8 receives the package, the following actions will be carried out:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>TP8 calls an <strong>updateShipment</strong> function that accepts the package uid and scanned key</li>\n<li>TP8 verifies that the key and the owner information is correct</li>\n<li>TP8 generates a new key with our custom <strong>genKey</strong> function and update the owner of the package to TP11</li>\n</ol>\n<p>When TP11 receives the package, the following actions will be carried out:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>TP11 calls an update function that accepts the package uid and scanned key</li>\n<li>TP11 verifies that the key and the owner information is correct</li>\n<li>TP11 marks the package as shipped and set keys/owner to None</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"blockchain-overview\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#blockchain-overview\" aria-label=\"blockchain overview permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Blockchain Overview</h2>\n<h3 id=\"entities\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#entities\" aria-label=\"entities permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Entities</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Manager: One account that manages a number of transit points and has the power to add or remove transit points. <em>Alternatives to a centralized entity?</em></li>\n<li>Transit Points: Each transit point has a unique id and serves as both a sender and receiver of packages. In the MVP, each originating transit point also sets the route and calls a blockchain function that creates a key for the next transit point. This key is used to generate a machine readable code at the transit points and this code is embedded in the physical package. At the reciving transit point and the machine readable code is read to reveal the key. The combination of correct key and the correct owner is used to verify the integrity of the package and that of the supply chain.</li>\n<li>Customers: In the MVP, customers can only access the state of the chain for the current location and status of the package.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"technical-design-todo\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#technical-design-todo\" aria-label=\"technical design todo permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Technical Design Todo</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Implement algorithm to choose route.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ol>\n<li>What routing algorithm should be chosen? Maybe DFS since its complexity could be O(N)</li>\n<li>Doing it off-chain or on-chain? If the algorithm is not too complexed, we could do on-chain.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"project\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#project\" aria-label=\"project permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Project</h2>\n<p>Visit <a href=\"https://github.com/Polkadot-DevCamp-2022/sub-tracker\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/-GitHub-0077B5?style=flat&#x26;logo=Github&#x26;logoColor=white&#x26;link=https://github.com/Polkadot-DevCamp-2022/sub-tracker/\" alt=\"Github Badge\"></a> to see the project</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Asset Tracking with Substrate Runtime","date":"May 30, 2022"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Portfolio/polkadot_dev_camp/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/Blockchain/\bsubstrate_frame/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Substrate FRAME"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/Portfolio/polkadot_staking_platform/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Polkadot Staking Curating Platform"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2486386679","3128451518"]}